title: Off-duty British-Israeli soldier flung back seven Hamas grenades before eighth blew up in his hand
description: An off-duty British-Israeli soldier threw back seven Hamas grenades targeted at a shelter by gunmen during the attack on a music festival on 7 October, Sky News has been told.

title: Family of Al Jazeera journalist reportedly killed in Israeli airstrike in Gaza
description: Al Jazeera has reported that the wife, son, and daughter of one of its correspondents in Gaza were killed in an Israeli airstrike on Wednesday night.

title: Hundreds of workers leave South African gold mine after three days being held 'hostage'
description: Hundreds of workers have left an underground gold mine in South Africa after being prevented from leaving for three days.

title: Family buries British mother and daughters who were killed in Hamas attack
description: In the cemetery of a small moshav, under the shade of the trees, a British mother and her two daughters were buried beneath the soil of Israel, in the land they made their home.

title: Trump fined $10,000 - before storming out of courtroom
description: Donald Trump has stormed out of a courtroom - having earlier been fined  $10,000 (£8,200) for breaching a gag order barring him from personally attacking court staff in his fraud trial.

title: Israel-Hamas ceasefire is 'untenable', says UK's defence secretary
description: Asking Israel to reach a ceasefire with Hamas is "untenable", the UK's defence secretary has said, as the number of MPs calling for a cessation of hostilities grows.

title: Netanyahu says he will have to 'answer for what happened' in Hamas attack
description: Israel Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said he will have to "answer for what happened" on 7 October as he addressed the nation.

title: Appeal begins after UK expat convicted of killing wife in Cyprus and then walked free from jail
description: Prosecutors in Cyprus have begun their appeal case against the verdict and sentence of a British expat who killed his seriously ill wife.

title: Mystery sudden deaths of endangered African elephants now solved, scientists say
description: A team of scientists say they have discovered what caused the sudden deaths of hundreds of elephants in Africa in 2020.

title: Activist could be sentenced to death in Iran as she faces imminent deportation from Turkey
description: An Iranian activist based in Turkey is in danger of imminent deportation to Iran, where she could face torture, interrogation, a lengthy sentence, and even capital punishment.

title: Hostage negotiations could be jeopardised by Gaza ground offensive, mediators warn
description: Negotiations to release more Hamas hostages from Gaza are ongoing but could be jeopardised by an Israeli ground offensive, Qatari mediators have warned.

title: How Gaza went from desperately poor to even poorer - and why that's important to the current war
description: The story we're currently seeing unfolding in Israel and Gaza at present doesn't seem to have much to do with economics. It's about murders, terrorism and missile attacks.

title: YouTuber apologises for fare dodging, begging and eating without paying in Japan
description: A YouTuber could be investigated by Japanese police after begging for cash and hitching free train rides in a video online.

title: Hospitals in Gaza forced to shut due to lack of fuel as Pope renews call for aid
description: One-third of hospitals in Gaza and nearly two-thirds of primary health care clinics have had to shut due to damage or lack of fuel, the United Nations (UN) has said.

title: Hezbollah and Hamas leaders meet as IDF spokesman urges world to 'rally around Israel'
description: The leader of Hezbollah has met with senior Hamas and Palestinian Islamic Jihad figures to discuss their aim of achieving a "real victory for the resistance in Gaza and Palestine", the Lebanese militant group has said.

title: British TikTok star jailed after trying to smuggle cocaine out of Peru
description: A British Tiktok star has been jailed for more than six years after being caught trying to smuggle cocaine into the UK.

title: Hamas warned delay to Gaza ground offensive has made Israeli troops 'more lethal'
description: There was a nervous energy at a dusty staging post for ground troops, waiting for an order to invade Gaza.

title: 'Catastrophic' storm hits Mexican beach resort town
description: A "catastrophic" tropical storm has strengthened to a Category 5 hurricane - making landfall in Mexico.

title: US spies believe hospital blast caused by Palestinian rocket that broke apart
description: US spy agencies believe the blast at a Gaza hospital a week ago was caused by a Palestinian rocket that suffered engine failure and broke apart into two pieces, with the warhead striking the hospital's parking lot, intelligence officials said on Tuesday.
